public abstract class AppResourceExistenceBOMImpl
extends BusinessObjectModuleImpl
implements ExistenceBOM

This is the Existence Business Object Module implementation for an AppResource BOM. A resource BOM consists of the resource in the specified locale, or any locale if none is specified. This class determines if an AppResource BOM exists on the target system.

Method Detail

isBusinessObjectExist

public boolean isBusinessObjectExist(BusinessObjectIdentifier businessObjectIdentifier,
                                     org.w3c.dom.Document boDocument)
                              throws AppException,
                                     InformationalException
This determines if an AppResource BOM exists on the database. The businessObjectIdentifier will contain the resource name and a locale form the unique identifier for a resource. This method will return true if the resources specified in the document exist in the target system, false otherwise.

Specified by:
isBusinessObjectExist in interface ExistenceBOM
Parameters:
businessObjectIdentifier - Contains the resource name and possibly the locale.
boDocument - Contains XML document representation of business object content.
Returns:
True if the resources specified in the document exist, false otherwise.
Throws:
AppException - Generic exception signature.
InformationalException - Generic exception signature.
